    <h1>Jakob Langtry — Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: May 2026</p>

    <p>
      This policy explains how Jakob Langtry handles information related to
      personal websites, projects, and optional SMS alerts from lab86.
    </p>

    <h2>Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>
      If you contact Jakob directly, opt in to SMS alerts, or interact with a
      project, we may collect the information you provide, such as your name,
      email address, phone number, message contents, and communication
      preferences.
    </p>

    <h2>SMS Alerts</h2>
    <p>
      SMS alerts are used for operational notifications, daily briefs, and
      direct responses related to Jakob's personal server and projects. Phone
      numbers are used only to deliver requested messages and manage opt-in,
      opt-out, and support requests.
    </p>

    <h2>No Sale of Personal Information</h2>
    <p>
      We do not sell, rent, or share phone numbers or SMS opt-in data with third
      parties for their marketing or promotional purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>Service Providers</h2>
    <p>
      We may use service providers, including messaging and hosting providers,
      to operate websites and deliver communications. These providers process
      information only as needed to provide those services.
    </p>

    <h2>Message Choices</h2>
    <p>
      You can reply STOP to unsubscribe from SMS messages. You can reply HELP
      for support information. Message and data rates may apply.
    </p>

    <h2>Data Retention</h2>
    <p>
      We keep communication records only as long as needed for operational,
      troubleshooting, security, or legal purposes.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact</h2>
    <p>
      Questions about this policy can be sent to
      <a href="mailto:jjalangtry@gmail.com">jjalangtry@gmail.com</a>.
    </p>
  </body>
